uk.ac.cf.cs.scm5mjw.mda.devices
Class ArtifactContainer

java.lang.Object
  uk.ac.cf.cs.scm5mjw.mda.devices.ArtifactContainer
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Iterable<Artifact>
public final class ArtifactContainer
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Iterable<Artifact>

This class handles storing a collection of Artifacts.
Internally, the collection is stored as a list and this class ensures that the list is sorted by artifact ID, thus allowing binarySearch to be used to support insertion, removal and searching.
Two Artifacts with the same resource ID are not allowed in the collection (i.e. all Artifacts in the collection have unique resource IDs).

An important feature of this class is that it also has a number of methods to aid in the tasks necessary for handling Artifacts in the mobile communication system.

add

public void add(Artifact newArt)
This method handles adding the Artifact newArt to the container. Note that it is illegal to add an Artifact which is older or the same age as an existing Artifact (given that both have the same resource ID).
If the Artifact being added is newer than an Artifact already in the container (given that both have the same resource ID), then older Artifact is replaced with the new one.

Note that the Artifact object is NOT copied.

addCopy

public void addCopy(Artifact newArt)
This method is the same as add( Artifact newArt ), except that the Artifact is copied and added (thus this will NOT result in another reference to the same Artifact object).

See Also:

copyAll

public void copyAll(java.util.List<Artifact> l)
This method will add a COPY of each Artifact in the given List to this ArtifactContainer. The addCopy method is used to handle adding each individual Artifact. There is not prerequisite ordering required of the input list. The addCopy method will handles placing the Artifact at the right location in the container.

See Also:
addCopy(uk.ac.cf.cs.scm5mjw.mda.devices.Artifact)

transferFrom

public java.util.List<Artifact> transferFrom(ArtifactContainer cont)
For the given ArtifactContainer cont, this method will return a list of all the Artifacts in b that are:
- not in this ArtifactContainer, or
- are newer (more recent) than the corresponding Artifact in this ArtifactContainer

Basically, this will give a list of all of the Artifacts that should be transferred from cont to this.

Also, the following code:
cont1.copyAll( cont1.transferFrom( cont2 ) )
will result in cont1 being updated to contain all of the Artifacts that need to be transferred from cont2.

Parameters:
cont - a container whose artifacts may be transferred to this artifact container
See Also:
copyAll(List)
